        <p>For the second visualization, I simplified the title and ensured it appears above the source credit to clearly indicate the context of the data. I also switched all fonts to Arial, following recommendations from the British Dyslexia Association's “Dyslexia Friendly Style Guide,” to make the visualization more accessible for individuals with dyslexia. The font sizes were also increased to 11-12 to improve readability.</p>
<p>Additionally, I revised the title to “General Government Debt of USMCA-Affiliated Countries” to specifically focus on the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and filtered the data to only include the United States, Mexico, and Canada. Below the title is the entirety of the acronym spelled out, for viewers who may not immediately connect "USMCA" to the full meaning. Since the U.S. has, as of the most recent years, the highest debt ratio, I applied a colorblind-friendly palette suitable for protanopia, a condition where distinguishing between red and green is difficult (Nichols, David). The color palette used includes the colors #525975 and #f8dc00. This helps emphasize the U.S. as having one of the highest debt-to-GDP ratios without making it difficult for potentially vision-impaired or colorblind individuals.

</p>

